\fs28 colibri Portal - Mac OS.X Installation Instructions for localhost development environment
\f0\b0\fs22 \ulnone \
******************************************************************************\

\f1\b The installation process has been tested under Mac OS X 10.8.3 (Mountain Lion)
\f0\b0 \
+*****************************************************************************\
\
\pard\tx220\tx720\tx1120\tx1680\tx2240\tx2800\tx3360\tx3920\tx4480\tx5040\tx5600\tx6160\tx6720\li720\fi-720\sl-300\pardirnatural
\ls1\ilvl0\cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	1.	}\kerning1\expnd1\expndtw6
First of all make sure you run a 
\f1\b Python 2.7.x
\f0\b0  version by running "
\f1\b python --version
\f0\b0 ". f you have a previous version or a version >2.7.x, then go and install Python 2.7 (Python is available at {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.python.org/download/releases/2.7/"}}{\fldrslt http://www.python.org/download/releases/2.7/}}\
\ls1\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	2.	}\kerning1\expnd1\expndtw6
Download 
\f1\b GIT
\f0\b0  from {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://git-scm.com/download/mac"}}{\fldrslt \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw6
http://git-scm.com/download/mac}}\
\ls1\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	3.	}\kerning1\expnd1\expndtw6
If you don't have 
\f1\b Xcode
\f0\b0  installed, download and install it from Mac App Store\
\ls1\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	4.	}\kerning1\expnd1\expndtw6
Open Xcode and then go to Preferences and install the "
\f1\b Command Line Tools
\f0\b0 " so that the gcc compiler is installed\
\ls1\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	5.	}\kerning1\expnd1\expndtw6
Open a terminal window, run "
\f1\b sudo easy_install pip
\f0\b0 " to install the pip installer.\
\ls1\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	6.	}\kerning1\expnd1\expndtw6
Clone the colibri git repository to a directory of your likings and browse to this directory from the terminal window.\
\ls1\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	7.	}\kerning1\expnd1\expndtw6
Once you are in the colibri directory, run "
\f1\b sudo pip install -r requirements.txt
\f0\b0 " in order to get all dependencies downloaded.\
\ls1\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	8.	}\kerning1\expnd1\expndtw6
To sync the DB, run "
\f1\b python manage.py syncdb
\f0\b0 " followed by "
\f1\b python manage.py migrate --fak
\f0\b0 e"\
\ls1\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	9.	}\kerning1\expnd1\expndtw6
At the end run "
\f1\b python manage.py runserver
\f0\b0 " to bring up the local server and with a browser go to {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://127.0.0.1:8000"}}{\fldrslt \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw6
http://127.0.0.1:8000}} to view the colibri portal\
\pard\tx560\tx1120\tx1680\tx2240\tx2800\tx3360\tx3920\tx4480\tx5040\tx5600\tx6160\tx6720\sl-300\pardirnatural
\cf0 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw6
\
\
Periodically, as new modules are added to the git repo of colibri, you should run steps 7-8 in order to download these new additions.\
\
\
