\f1\b C:\\Python27\\folder
\f0\b0  (don't copy the whole folder into it, just the content), because the python command doesn't work outside 
\f1\b C:\\Python2x
\f0\b0  folder and then run "
\f1\b python setup.py install
\f0\b0 "\
